Claire H. Babrowski  Director, Pier 1 Imports, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships60$170,907
Background

		Ms. Claire H. Babrowski served as an Executive Vice President and Chief Operating Officer of Toys "R" Us Inc., from June 1, 2007 to May 2010. Ms. Babrowski served as an Acting Chief Executive Officer of RadioShack Corp., from February 2006 to July 5, 2006 and served as its President since February 2006. She served as Executive Officer of Toys 'R' US Property Company I, LLC until May 1, 2010. She served as a Chief Operating Officer of RadioShack Corp. since July 2005, ... where she oversaw U.S. and Canadian operations, including channel operations, merchandising, marketing & advertising, retail services and real estate. She served as an Executive Vice President of Radioshack Corp., from July 5, 2005 to February 2006. She served as Corporate Senior Executive Vice President and Chief Restaurant Operations Officer of McDonald's Corporation from December 2003 to December 2004. She began her career as a McDonald's Crewmember and advanced over the next 30 years and worked as its highest-ranking female executive including its Restaurant Manager and Regional Vice President (in the early 1990s). In 1995, she was promoted to her first corporate role, where she led the development of McDonald's technology plan to support McDonald's restaurant of the future. She served as an Executive Vice President of Worldwide Restaurant Systems from January 2000 to June 2001 and from June 2001 to December 2003, President of McDonald's Asia/Pacific, Middle East and South Africa operations, where she held direct responsibility for 7,500 restaurants, including market development, restaurant operations, financial performance and brand development. Ms. Babrowski served as an Executive Vice President of U.S. Restaurant Systems from June 1998 to January 2000 and as its Senior Vice President, U.S. Restaurant Systems from May 1997 to June 1998. She has been a Director of Pier 1 Imports, Inc. since March 25, 2011; and Pier 1 Imports, Inc., since March 25, 2011. She served as an Independent Director at Etablissements Delhaize Freres et Cie "Le Lion" S.A. since May 2006 until May 26, 2016. She received the Emerging Leader Award from the U.S. Women's Service Forum, in 1998. She is a member of the Committee of 200, a professional U.S. organization of preeminent women entrepreneurs and corporate leaders. Ms. Babrowski holds a Master of Business Administration degree from the University of North Carolina.Read Full Background




